250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
½ cup Marinara Sauce
2 tbsp Caesar Dressing
28 g Croutons
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Lettuce
30 g Mixed Olives
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Core, then cut peppers into 1/4-inch slices.
Roll sausage into 6 (12) equal-sized meatballs, then press to flatten into1/2-inch patties.

To a foil-lined baking sheet, add peppers and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Add sausage patties on top of peppers.
Broil in the middle of the oven for 8-10 min, until patties are cooked through.

When the peppers are done, halve buns. Arrange on another baking sheet, cut-sides up. Sprinkle mozzarella cheese over tops of buns.
Spread 2 tbsp marinara sauce over bottom buns.
Broil buns in the top of the oven for 4-5 min, until cheese melts. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Cut romaine lettuce into 1-inch pices.
Drain, then roughly chop olives.
To a large bowl, add lettuce, Caesar dressing, croutons, olives and Parmesan cheese. Season with pepper, then toss to combine.

Top bottom buns with patties, peppers and top buns.
Divide Italian sausage sammies and Caesar salad between plates.
Serve any remaining marinara sauce on the side for dipping.